title: John Serle (MP for Plympton Erle)
text: John Serle (<a href="floruit">fl.</a> 1414–1449) of <a href="Plympton">Plympton</a>, <a href="Devon">Devon</a>, was an English <a href="Member%20of%20Parliament">Member of Parliament</a> for <a href="Plympton%20Erle%20%28UK%20Parliament%20constituency%29">Plympton Erle</a> in November 1414, 1431, 1432, 1433, 1435, 1437, 1442 and February 1449.
